headline: Trump announces trade deal, BoE lowers Bank Rate: Morning Buzz
summary: The major averages were sharply higher near noon amid increased optimism around trade, as well as a decrease in U.S. initial jobless claims for the week ended May 3. President Trump announced a new trade deal with Great Britain, has said the U.S. intends to “make a deal with Europe,” and appears open to lowering tariffs on China after talks with the country this weekend.
